                <note rend="inline" type="source">721.23/2152: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Peru</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dearing</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-03-26T17:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 26, 1934—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>23. Your 36, March 24, 1 p.m., last sentence. What are the “developments”
                    mentioned in the reports in question?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
